1. Follow this directory structure:
```
app/
├── Http/
│   ├── Controllers/
│   │   └── Api/
│   │       ├── V1/
│   │       └── V2/
│   ├── Requests/
│   │   └── Api/
│   ├── Resources/
│   │   └── Api/
│   └── Middleware/
├── Services/
│   ├── Contracts/
│   └── Concretes/
├── Repositories/
│   ├── Contracts/
│   └── Concretes/
├── Models/
├── Traits/
└── Providers/
```
2. Use Laravel's built-in features and best practices.
3. Follow Laravel's coding standards and conventions.
4. Follow SOLID principles.
5. Use meaningful variable names and comments.
6. Use meaningful function names and comments.
7. Use meaningful class names and comments.
8. Use meaningful file names and comments.
9. Use meaningful directory names and comments.
10. Use meaningful namespace names and comments.
11. Use meaningful method names and comments.
12. Use meaningful parameter names and comments.
13. Add documentation for all classes, methods, and functions.
